#
# We could use "read" with an IFS, but "read" in POSIX does not handle quoted text.
#

# Parse in POSIX mode using text from stdin (xargs handles this internally)
# Split by newline, not space/tab.
#
# By default, xargs will parse the entire input and
# use the first 100KiB or so.
#
# Large inputs may fail with "argument list too long".

# The following works around the problem and also makes the command compatible
# with "busybox" xargs.

# Create an input that uses newlines only.
#
# Without the final newline, "set --" would create an empty arg which is discarded,
# which is good because we don't want an empty arg.
